Title: Task Assignment List

- Backend: Implement Core API & DB

  Labels: backend, api, high
  Branch: feature/backend-core
  Overview: Implement DB schema, ORM models, init_db.py, and REST endpoints for employees, attendance, and payroll calculation.

  Checklist:
Define DB schema / ER diagram
Implement ORM models in models
Create init_db.py migrations/setup
Implement core routes in app.py (employees, attendance, salary)
Implement payroll & salary calculation logic
Add unit tests for core business logic
Document API endpoints (OpenAPI/README)

  Acceptance Criteria: Endpoints return JSON for CRUD flows; init_db.py initializes DB cleanly; payroll unit tests pass.

- Frontend: Templates & Styling

  Labels: frontend, ui, medium
  Branch: feature/frontend-ui
  Overview: Polish templates and responsive styles; build accessible forms for admin and employee flows.

  Checklist:
Improve layout in templates, admin, employee
Implement responsive styles in style.css
Build add/edit employee and attendance forms with client-side validation
Ensure accessibility and mobile views
Integrate templates with backend endpoints

  Acceptance Criteria: Templates render correctly for roles; forms validate client-side and submit to backend.

- Auth & Security: Login, RBAC, Hardening

  Labels: security, auth, high
  Branch: feature/auth-security
  Overview: Implement secure register/login, password hashing, sessions, role-based access control, and basic hardening (CSRF, input validation).

  Checklist:
Implement register/login in auth.py
Use password hashing (e.g., bcrypt) and secure session cookies
Implement RBAC (admin vs employee) for protected routes
Add CSRF protection and input validation
Add tests for auth flows and protected routes

  Acceptance Criteria: Secure login/register; admin-only routes blocked for employee roles; auth tests pass.

- Features: Admin & Employee CRUD Flows

  Labels: feature, admin, employee
  Branch: feature/admin-employee
  Overview: Implement admin CRUD for employees and attendance; employee-facing views and salary reporting.

  Checklist:
Implement admin CRUD for employees (admin.py)
Implement attendance add/edit/delete flows and templates
Implement employee views (employee.py)
Wire salary generation/reporting to templates
Add end-to-end tests for major flows

  Acceptance Criteria: Admin can perform CRUD operations and generate reports; UI and DB stay in sync.

- QA / Docs / DevOps: Tests, README, CI

  Labels: docs, ci, testing
  Branch: chore/qa-docs-devops
  Overview: Provide tests, documentation, pinned deps, and CI suggestion for the project.

  Checklist:
Add unit and integration tests (pytest)
Update README.md with run and deployment instructions
Pin dependencies in requirements.txt
Add simple run scripts / local setup instructions
Provide GitHub Actions workflow example for tests

  Acceptance Criteria: Tests run locally and in CI; README contains clear setup/run steps.
